STANDARD LUMBER COMPANY
OPERATING
RETAIL LUMBER AND COALYARD
GENERAL OFFICE
WINONA, MINNESOTA
ROSCOE HORTON, President
FRANK HORTON, Vice President
R.H Jackson, VicePres & Gen Mgr
W. E HEIDEL, Treasurer
H.S. HORTON, Secretary
October 10th 1930
Dr. Graham Taylor
Chicago Commons
Chicago, Ill
Dear Doctor Taylor
[Thou quick] recently finished reading aloud to Mrs. Horton your book "Pioneering on Social Frontiers" and we both wish to tell you how much we enjoyed following you through your years of active work.
